name: CNN
text: "All the women who have worked to secure and protect the right to vote for over a century ... I stand on their shoulders," Vice President-elect Kamala Harris says. "...But while I may be the first woman in this office, I will not be the last." https://t.co/wPcVmefUYG https://t.co/8MbQXziL5X

name: CNN
text: Vice President-elect Kamala Harris: "For four years, you marched and organized for equality and justice, for our lives and for our planet and then you voted. And you delivered a clear message. You chose hope and unity, decency, science and, yes, truth." https://t.co/bcbtfR7EGD https://t.co/EIV7YtFW2r

name: CNN
text: President-elect Joe Biden: “I pledge to be a president who seeks not to divide but unify — who doesn’t see red states and blue states, only sees the United States.” https://t.co/NVSF3oVh4E https://t.co/iFAIu9J0j9

name: CNN
text: President-elect Joe Biden: "For all those of you who voted for President Trump, I understand the disappointment tonight. I've lost a couple times myself. But now, let's give each other a chance." https://t.co/5s01RnP7M0 https://t.co/wjxQBtDNFR

name: CNN
text: "Our nation is shaped by the constant battle between our better angels and our darkest impulses. And what presidents say in this battle matters," President-elect Joe Biden said. "...I believe at our best, America is a beacon for the globe." https://t.co/VY9SepVZta https://t.co/75OWlnr028

name: CNN
text:
“Sky Full of Stars” by Coldplay was played during Joe Biden's event — a song by one of Beau Biden’s favorite bands.

At Beau’s 2015 funeral, Coldplay’s Chris Martin performed “'Til Kingdom Come.” Martin offered to perform after learning that Beau was a fan https://t.co/TA46UItZ3q
